        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33279",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=juokaz",
                        "name": "juokaz",
                        "displayName": "Juozas Kaziukenas",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "I have few sollutions in mind, but only one work for me: having Date object cast to sting. Its quite easy in all calls to check if returned value is date object and then return value as a string representation. \nI don't think that using sqlsrv_get_field for all fields is a good idea. Basically you will end-up with exponentially increasing load. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=juokaz",
                        "name": "juokaz",
                        "displayName": "Juozas Kaziukenas",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-07T02:02:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-07T02:02:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33280",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dcaunt",
                        "name": "dcaunt",
                        "displayName": "David Caunt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree Juozas, I think this is the most efficient way to handle the problem. The overhead in building a string from the DateTime should be minimal.\n\nMany thanks",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dcaunt",
                        "name": "dcaunt",
                        "displayName": "David Caunt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-07T02:46:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-07T02:46:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33712",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=the_angry_angel",
                        "name": "the_angry_angel",
                        "displayName": "Karl Southern",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It might be worth noting that with the very recent Sqlsrv 1.1 CTP there is now an option to return all datetime values as strings, which you can pass into the driver_options of your DB config\n\nhttp:\/\/social.msdn.microsoft.com\/Forums\/en-US\/sqldriverforphp\/thread\/42503986-b14b-4301-b142-96f8275ebc7a\n\nhttp:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ee376928%28SQL.90%29.aspx",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=the_angry_angel",
                        "name": "the_angry_angel",
                        "displayName": "Karl Southern",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-21T03:58:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-21T03:58:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33717",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dcaunt",
                        "name": "dcaunt",
                        "displayName": "David Caunt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Excellent. I wonder if this option should be enabled by default, so this adapter functions as per other Zend_Db_Adapters?\n\nIn testing the 1.1 version, I was required to update my SQL Server Native Client component. The link given in the exception was wrong (outdated), however and I found the latest version at http:\/\/go.microsoft.com\/fwlink\/?LinkId=123717&clcid=0x409 via http:\/\/www.microsoft.com\/downloads\/details.aspx?displaylang=en&FamilyID=c6c3e9ef-ba29-4a43-8d69-a2bed18fe73c",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dcaunt",
                        "name": "dcaunt",
                        "displayName": "David Caunt",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-21T06:31:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-21T06:31:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33902",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has been fixed at the driver level by Microsoft in later versions of their sqlsrv driver.  It is sugguested you upgrade to 1.1 of the sql server driver.\n\n-ralph",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-25T12:20:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-25T12:20:00.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
